[size=4][u]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD for Star Wars Interworlds adoption mod by Chem[/u][/size]

This patch mod makes possible to load the [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] after [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b]. This will give you possibility to use all latest features of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] in comparison with embedded one.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Replaces only one [b]content.xml[/b] file of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] to ensure the loading order.
[*] Does not change any content of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b], so you will get all latest features of it.
[*] Makes possible to use newest (in comparison with embedded) version of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] with [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b].
[/list]
[size=3][u][b]Installation[/b][/u][/size]

This mod can be installed in three ways - manual installation, Vortex installation and Collection installation. Please choose the one that suits you best.

First two methods can be done via downloading the mod from its page on [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2134]Nexus Mods[/url].

[size=3][u][i]Manual Installation[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Install [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b] and [b]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mods first.
[*] Download the latest version of the mod from the Nexus Mods page.
[*] Extract the downloaded archive to [b]extensions[/b] folder of your X4 installation directory with overwriting the only one file in it - [b]content.xml[/b].
[*] You should repeat this process every time when you will update the [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod!
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Vortex Installation[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Install [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b] and [b]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mods first.
[*] Download the latest version of the mod from the Nexus Mods page using Vortex.
[*] You will get a notification about file conflict.
[/list]  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/x4-mod-ui-extensions-for-swi/refs/heads/main/docs/images/file_conflict.png[/img]
[list][*] Click on "More" button and you will see something like this:
[/list]  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/x4-mod-ui-extensions-for-swi/refs/heads/main/docs/images/file_conflict_details.png[/img]
[list][*] Click on "Show" button and you have possibility to set a rule for the extensions.
[*] Please set the rule like this, i.e. make the [b]UI Extensions and HUD for SW Interworlds adoption mod[/b] to load always after [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod:
[/list]  [img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/x4-mod-ui-extensions-for-swi/refs/heads/main/docs/images/file_conflict_rule.png[/img]
[list][*] Setting a rule is required only for the first time!
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Collection Installation[/i][/u][/size]

Collection installation can be done via Collection Page on [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/games/x4foundations/collections/4lmz4]Nexus Mods[/url].

This collection contains only two mods:
[list]
[*] [b]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD[/b] - latest version of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod.
[*] [b]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD for SW Interworlds adoption mod[/b] - this mod.
[/list]
There is one reason to make this collection - to ensure the loading order of mods. It contains the rule which makes the [b]UI Extensions and HUD for SW Interworlds adoption mod[/b] overwrite the original [b]content.xml[/b] file of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod. So, you will get all latest features of [b]UI Extensions and HUD[/b] mod with [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b] mod.

[size=3][u][i]Verification[/i][/u][/size]

After successful installation you should see a next picture in the extensions menu:

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/x4-mod-ui-extensions-for-swi/refs/heads/main/docs/images/success.png[/img]

[size=3][u][b]Compatibility[/b][/u][/size]

This mod currently oriented on a X4: Foundations version 8.00 with latest hotfixes, as there is a latest version supported by [b]Star Wars Interworlds[/b] mod.

